OL,3,CDoctor tells murder trial boy's burns
OL,4,Clooked like 'inflicted injury'
OL,6,FShe denies murder and child cruelty.
OL,8,FDr Lekshmi Nair, a consultant
OL,9,Fpaediatrician at the University
OL,10,FHospital of North Durham, helped to
OL,11,Ftreat Dwelaniyah on 5 November 2022.
OL,12,FShe also examined his body after he
OL,13,Fwas declared dead.
OL,15,FShe told Newcastle Crown Court on
OL,16,FMonday (4 March) that she formed the
OL,17,Fopinion that the boy's body had
OL,18,F"extensive burns, scratches and
OL,19,Fbruises of a non accidental nature
OL,20,Fwhich indicated neglect".
