OL,3,CDoctor tells murder trial boy's burns
OL,4,Clooked like 'inflicted injury'
OL,6,FThe court has previously heard a
OL,7,Frecording of Robinson telling Dr Nair
OL,8,Fthat the burns had been caused when he
OL,9,Fwas messing about in the shower a few
OL,10,Fweeks earlier.
OL,12,FHowever, the doctor told the court
OL,13,Fthat "the appearance of the burns is
OL,14,Fnot consistent with the explanation
OL,15,Fgiven by the mother," adding, "they
OL,16,Fhave the appearance of an inflicted
OL,17,Finjury".
