OL,3,CDoctor tells murder trial boy's burns
OL,4,Clooked like 'inflicted injury'
OL,6,FShe explained that "there were no
OL,7,Fsplash marks" on his body, adding: "If
OL,8,Fhe'd been playing with the shower I
OL,9,Fwould have expected splash marks."
OL,11,FDr Nair also said there were "very
OL,12,Fneat lines on the outside of the burn"
OL,13,Fwhich, she said suggested it was an
OL,14,F"inflicted injury".
OL,16,FShe described the burns as "indicative
OL,17,Fof an immersion injury, where the
OL,18,Fchild is held in hot, boiling water,
OL,19,Fcausing those burns".
