OL,3,CDoctor tells murder trial boy's burns
OL,4,Clooked like 'inflicted injury'
OL,6,FIn addition, she said a culture from a
OL,7,Fswab of the burns grew bacteria which
OL,8,Fshowed that it was "it was an unclean
OL,9,Fand untreated wound".
OL,11,FShe told the court that a child with
OL,12,Fsuch extensive burns "should have been
OL,13,Fadmitted to a burns unit".
OL,15,FThe court has been told that
OL,17,FDr Nair said that there were "linear
OL,18,Fmarks" on his body which were
OL,19,F"suggestive of being struck by a long
OL,20,Fimplement with a high velocity".
